  <title>Working with Test Cases</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="testSpecificationViewContextId">Test Case Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="problemViewContextId">Problem View</anchor>
  <para>
    Test Cases are the ”building blocks” (keywords) for testing. They
    can:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        contain other (referenced) Test Cases (<xref linkend="adding-items-to-editors"/>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        contain Test Steps (<xref linkend="specsteps"/>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        be used in Test Suites (<xref linkend="adding-items-to-editors"/>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        be used as Event Handlers (<xref linkend="dealing-with-errors-in-tests"/>)
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  
